FT  18 SEP 92 / Law firm retains earnings title
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT RICE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SLAUGHTER and May, the City solicitors, has maintained its position as the
UK's most profitable law firm in the year to March, according to an earnings
league table published yesterday by the magazine Legal Business, Robert Rice
writes.
The firm had average net profit per partner of Pounds 390,000 on turnover of
Pounds 113m, and profit per fee earner (lawyer) of Pounds 67,000. It has 567
fee earners. Slaughter and May has increased profitability against flat
turnover. Last year it had average net profit per partner of Pounds 377,000
on turnover of Pounds 113m.
Its nearest rival was again Linklaters &amp; Paines, with average net profit of
Pounds 380,000 on turnover of Pounds 154m, and profit per fee earner of
Pounds 75,000. Linklaters has 718 fee earners.
The figures show that in general Britain's top law firms appear to be
surviving the recession well. The magazine says gross revenues have
increased slightly and profits have remained high. The top 35 firms had a
combined turnover of more than Pounds 2bn.
