FT  17 SEP 92 / The ERM and Britain: Use of Parliament
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PARLIAMENT has been recalled from recess on 10 occasions since the second
world war. Parliament is normally recalled in times of national emergency,
sudden political crisis or when approval is required for the despatch of
troops into possible conflict. The Tories have rejected requests from the
Labour leader for a recall of parliament at least five times since in 1979.
