<HEADLINE>
FT  17 SEP 92 / Botnar's group wins Fiat deal: AFG gains further car
franchise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN DONE, Motor Industry Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AUTOMOTIVE and Financial Group (AFG), the motor retailer controlled by Mr
Octav Botnar, has succeeded in gaining the Fiat group franchise for 25 of
its dealerships.
AFG is quickly becoming one of the top three multi-franchise UK dealer
groups and has gained franchises from at least seven leading carmakers.
The future of the group was placed at risk when Nissan UK, its sister
company, lost the lucrative Nissan importer/distributor franchise at the end
of last year as a consequence of the legal conflict between Mr Botnar and
Nissan Motor, the Japanese carmaker.
Mr Botnar, chairman and managing director of Automotive Financial Group
Holdings, the holding company for AFG, is in Switzerland. He was abroad when
a warrant was issued for his arrest by the Inland Revenue at the end of
January, and he has not since returned to the UK.
AFG was previously the largest UK motor retailer, with about 160 sites, but
sold exclusively Nissan new vehicles. The loss of Nissan forced it to
undertake drastic restructuring in an effort to find replacement franchises.
The group has succeeded in refranchising at least 68 of its UK dealerships
and it has emerged as the largest UK dealer group for three European
carmakers - Fiat, Renault and Citroen.
Under the Fiat franchise, the dealerships are largely dual franchises
consisting of either Fiat-Alfa Romeo or Fiat-Lancia.
AFG has also secured the Citroen franchise for 14 dealerships, Renault and
Peugeot for 11 each, Vauxhall for four (with one additional dealership under
discussion), Honda for two and Volkswagen/Audi for one.
The restructuring of the AFG network into a multi-franchise group and the
build-up by Nissan Motor of its own dealer network has caused a considerable
upheaval in the UK retail motor trade.
Nissan Motor's network of dealers was opened with 150 outlets at the
beginning of the year and is planned to expand to a total of 250 to 270
dealers by the end of the year.
</TEXT>
